<subSubSection id="48D355CA8EDEFF5048A7531BFE2BF922" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418EDEFF5048A7531BFEB2FBBF" blockId="144.[151,1436,1045,1891]" box="[151,279,1079,1103]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EDEFF504890531BFEABFBBF" box="[160,270,1079,1103]" captionStart="PLATE 38" captionStartId="145.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,208,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-116@145.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionText="PLATE 38. A, B, D–I. Male genitalia, holotypes. C. Chela. A, B. Anteon nemorale (from Olmi 1984). C. A. nepalense, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. A. ningshanense (from Xu et al. 2012a). E. A. pahanganum (from Olmi 1991). F. A. pangi (from Xu et al. 1998). G. A. papillatum (from Olmi 2000b). H. A. papillum (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). I. A. parapriscum (from Olmi 1991). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A and B, 0.16 mm for C and I, 0.28 mm for D and H, 0.21 mm for E and G, 0.23 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278506/files/figure.png" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Plate 38C</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418EDEFF5048A753ACFD6FFB66" blockId="144.[151,1436,1045,1891]" box="[151,714,1152,1174]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Anteon nepalense Olmi 1984: 304; Olmi 1998e: 48, 49.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418EDEFF5048A753EEFE6AF95E" blockId="144.[151,1436,1045,1891]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
Description of Female. Fully winged; length 2.8–3.0 mm. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna brown; mesosoma and metasoma black; legs testaceous, except coxae and clubs of femora darkened. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 10:6:9:6:5:6:6:6:5:6. Head shiny, punctate, unsculptured among punctures; face with two lateral keels near orbits directed towards antennal toruli; frontal line present; occipital carina complete; POL = 5; OL = 4; OOL = 4.5; OPL = 3.5; TL = 3; temple present. Pronotum shiny, with anterior surface rugose; posterior surface shiny, smooth, unsculptured, shorter than scutum (6:13); pronotal tubercle reaching tegula. Scutum shiny, smooth, finely punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.65 length of scutum (Fig. 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EDEFF504BB55292FC67FA26" box="[901,962,1470,1494]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" unit="in" value="23.0">23 in</quantity>
Olmi 1998e). Scutellum and metanotum shiny, smooth, unsculptured. Propodeum reticulate rugose, with strong transverse keel between dorsal and posterior surface; posterior surface with two longitudinal keels and median area as rugose as lateral areas. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein shorter than proximal part (3:11). Protarsal segments in following proportions: 8:3:2:4:13. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EDEFF504B525162FC74F996" box="[866,977,1614,1638]" captionStart="PLATE 38" captionStartId="145.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,208,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-116@145.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionText="PLATE 38. A, B, D–I. Male genitalia, holotypes. C. Chela. A, B. Anteon nemorale (from Olmi 1984). C. A. nepalense, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. A. ningshanense (from Xu et al. 2012a). E. A. pahanganum (from Olmi 1991). F. A. pangi (from Xu et al. 1998). G. A. papillatum (from Olmi 2000b). H. A. papillum (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). I. A. parapriscum (from Olmi 1991). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A and B, 0.16 mm for C and I, 0.28 mm for D and H, 0.21 mm for E and G, 0.23 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278506/files/figure.png" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Plate 38C</figureCitation>
) with proximal prominence bearing one long bristle. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EDEFF504A0F515EFD0AF97A" box="[575,687,1650,1674]" captionStart="PLATE 38" captionStartId="145.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,208,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-116@145.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionText="PLATE 38. A, B, D–I. Male genitalia, holotypes. C. Chela. A, B. Anteon nemorale (from Olmi 1984). C. A. nepalense, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. A. ningshanense (from Xu et al. 2012a). E. A. pahanganum (from Olmi 1991). F. A. pangi (from Xu et al. 1998). G. A. papillatum (from Olmi 2000b). H. A. papillum (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). I. A. parapriscum (from Olmi 1991). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A and B, 0.16 mm for C and I, 0.28 mm for D and H, 0.21 mm for E and G, 0.23 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278506/files/figure.png" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Plate 38C</figureCitation>
) with one row of about 15 lamellae; distal apex with about seven lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418EDEFF5048F75197FE2BF922" blockId="144.[151,1436,1045,1891]" box="[199,398,1722,1747]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
